From: "Lorenzo Stoakes (Oracle)" <ljs@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 11:22:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mm-huge_memory-add-and-use-normal_or_softleaf_folio_pmd-fix

avoid bisection hazard

Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/d0cc6161-77a4-42ba-a411-96c23c78df1b@lucifer.local
Signed-off-by: Lorenzo Stoakes (Oracle) <ljs@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
---
 mm/huge_memory.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/huge_memory.c b/mm/huge_memory.c
index c3e44c2bee88..ade49830c699 100644
--- a/mm/huge_memory.c
+++ b/mm/huge_memory.c
@@ -2481,7 +2481,7 @@ bool zap_huge_pmd(struct mmu_gather *tlb, struct vm_area_struct *vma,
 		zap_huge_pmd_folio(mm, vma, orig_pmd, folio, is_present,
 				   &has_deposit);
 	else if (is_huge_zero_pmd(orig_pmd))
-		has_deposit = !vma_is_dax(vma);
+		has_deposit = has_deposit || !vma_is_dax(vma);
 
 	if (has_deposit)
 		zap_deposited_table(mm, pmd);
-- 
2.47.3

